5000|$|<b>Radiant</b> <b>barriers</b> (also {{known as}} {{reflective}} insulation) are {{a type of}} thermal (heat) insulations that prevents heat transfer by thermal radiation. Thermal energy may also be transferred via conduction or convection, however, and <b>radiant</b> <b>barriers</b> do not necessarily protect against heat transfer via conduction (without airspace facing the heat source) or convection (perforated).|$|R
