50|$|<b>Radiant</b> <b>barrier</b> {{may be used}} as a vented {{skin around}} the {{exterior}} of a wall. Furring strips are applied to the sheathing to create a vented air space between the <b>radiant</b> <b>barrier</b> and the siding, and vents are used at the top and bottom to allow convective heat to rise naturally to the attic. If brick is being used on the exterior, then a vented air space may already be present, and furring strips are not necessary. Wrapping a house with <b>radiant</b> <b>barrier</b> can result in a 10% to 20% reduction in the tonnage air conditioning system requirement, and save both energy and construction costs.|$|E
